                    <div class="document-header">
                        <h3 class="document-title">CODE OF CONDUCT</h3>
                        <div>
                            <span class="document-category">Governance</span>
                            <span class="document-meta">Last updated: January 10, 2025</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="document-content">
                        <p>This Code of Conduct outlines the expectations for all members, volunteers, and participants in T.S.K.V. Spartacus activities. By joining our association, you agree to uphold these principles.</p>
                        
                        <h3>RESPECT AND INCLUSION</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Treat all members, guests, and staff with respect regardless of age, gender, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, race, ethnicity, or religion.</li>
                            <li>Use inclusive language and be mindful of the diverse backgrounds within our community.</li>
                            <li>Refrain from any form of harassment, discrimination, or bullying.</li>
                            <li>Support and encourage fellow members in their strength sports journey.</li>
                            <li>Respect the training space and the needs of others using the facilities.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>SPORTSMANSHIP</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Demonstrate good sportsmanship in training and competition settings.</li>
                            <li>Celebrate the achievements of others and offer constructive feedback when appropriate.</li>
                            <li>Accept victories graciously and losses with dignity.</li>
                            <li>Adhere to the rules and regulations of competitions.</li>
                            <li>Represent T.S.K.V. Spartacus positively when participating in external events.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>SAFETY AND WELLBEING</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Prioritize safety in all training activities and follow established safety guidelines.</li>
                            <li>Use equipment properly and report any damages or malfunctions.</li>
                            <li>Assist others with spotting when requested and appropriate.</li>
                            <li>Never train under the influence of alcohol or recreational drugs.</li>
                            <li>Report any unsafe conditions or behaviors to association leadership.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>INTEGRITY</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Adhere to anti-doping policies and promote clean sport.</li>
                            <li>Be honest about your abilities and limitations.</li>
                            <li>Respect the decisions of coaches, referees, and association leadership.</li>
                            <li>Follow all rules established by Tilburg University Sports Center.</li>
                            <li>Represent yourself and the association with honesty and integrity.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>COMMUNICATION</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Communicate openly and respectfully with all members.</li>
                            <li>Address conflicts directly and constructively with the parties involved.</li>
                            <li>Provide feedback through appropriate channels.</li>
                            <li>Respect the primary language of the association (English) to ensure inclusivity for international members.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>ENFORCEMENT</h3>
                        <p>Violations of this Code of Conduct may result in actions ranging from verbal warnings to membership termination, depending on the severity and frequency of the violation. The Board of T.S.K.V. Spartacus is responsible for enforcing this code and addressing reported violations.</p>
                    </div>
