                <!-- Bylaws -->
                <div class="document-card" id="bylaws" data-category="governance">
                    <div class="document-header">
                        <h3 class="document-title">BYLAWS</h3>
                        <div>
                            <span class="document-category">Governance</span>
                            <span class="document-meta">Last updated: December 5, 2024</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="document-content">
                        <p>The bylaws of T.S.K.V. Spartacus establish the official structure, governance, and operational procedures of our association. These bylaws are binding for all members and activities.</p>
                        
                        <h3>ARTICLE I: NAME AND PURPOSE</h3>
                        <p>The name of this organization is Tilburgse Studenten Kracht Sport Vereniging Spartacus (T.S.K.V. Spartacus). The purpose of this association is to promote strength sports among students at Tilburg University, provide training facilities and guidance, organize competitions, and foster a supportive community for members.</p>
                        
                        <h3>ARTICLE II: MEMBERSHIP</h3>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Membership is open to all students enrolled at Tilburg University. Alumni and staff may be granted membership at the discretion of the Board.</li>
                            <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Membership is valid for one academic year (September 1 to August 31).</li>
                            <li><strong>Fees:</strong> Annual membership fees are determined by the Board and approved at the General Assembly.</li>
                            <li><strong>Rights:</strong> Members have the right to participate in all association activities, use designated facilities, vote in General Assemblies, and stand for election to the Board.</li>
                            <li><strong>Termination:</strong> Membership may be terminated by resignation, failure to pay dues, or expulsion for violations of the Code of Conduct.</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h3>ARTICLE III: GOVERNANCE</h3>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>Board:</strong> The association is governed by an elected Board consisting of at least a President, Secretary, and Treasurer, with additional positions as needed.</li>
                            <li><strong>Elections:</strong> Board elections are held annually during the General Assembly in May/June.</li>
                            <li><strong>Term:</strong> Board members serve for one academic year with the possibility of re-election.</li>
                            <li><strong>Duties:</strong> The Board is responsible for day-to-day operations, financial management, member relations, and representing the association.</li>
                            <li><strong>Committees:</strong> The Board may establish committees for specific purposes (e.g., competition committee, social committee).</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h3>ARTICLE IV: MEETINGS</h3>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>General Assembly:</strong> Held at least twice annually (September and May/June).</li>
                            <li><strong>Special Meetings:</strong> May be called by the Board or by petition of at least 25% of members.</li>
                            <li><strong>Quorum:</strong> At least 15% of members must be present for binding decisions.</li>
                            <li><strong>Voting:</strong> Each member has one vote; decisions are made by simple majority except for bylaw amendments.</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h3>ARTICLE V: FINANCES</h3>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>Fiscal Year:</strong> September 1 to August 31.</li>
                            <li><strong>Budget:</strong> Prepared by the Treasurer, approved by the Board, and presented at the September General Assembly.</li>
                            <li><strong>Audit:</strong> Financial records are audited annually by an Audit Committee appointed by the General Assembly.</li>
                            <li><strong>Expenditures:</strong> Board approval is required for unbudgeted expenses exceeding €100.</li>
                        </ol>
                        
