                <!-- Safety Guidelines -->
                <div class="document-card" id="safety-guidelines" data-category="safety">
                    <div class="document-header">
                        <h3 class="document-title">SAFETY GUIDELINES</h3>
                        <div>
                            <span class="document-category">Safety</span>
                            <span class="document-meta">Last updated: November 15, 2024</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="document-content">
                        <p>Safety is our highest priority at T.S.K.V. Spartacus. These guidelines establish standards for safe training practices and must be followed by all members during all association activities.</p>
                        
                        <h3>GENERAL SAFETY</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Always warm up properly before beginning strength training.</li>
                            <li>Start with lighter weights to establish proper technique before progressing to heavier loads.</li>
                            <li>Never train alone when attempting maximal or near-maximal lifts.</li>
                            <li>Use proper spotters for exercises that require them (bench press, squat, etc.).</li>
                            <li>If you're unsure about proper technique, ask an experienced member or coach for guidance.</li>
                            <li>Report any equipment issues or facility hazards immediately to the Board or Sports Center staff.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>EQUIPMENT USAGE</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Inspect all equipment before use for damage or wear.</li>
                            <li>Always use collars/clips on barbells when appropriate.</li>
                            <li>Return all equipment to its designated storage area after use.</li>
                            <li>Wipe down equipment after use with the provided cleaning supplies.</li>
                            <li>Do not drop weights unless using designated platforms and bumper plates.</li>
                            <li>Use appropriate lifting belts, wraps, and other supportive equipment correctly.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>SPOTTING</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Always offer a spot when someone requests one.</li>
                            <li>Communicate clearly with the lifter about their expectations for the spot.</li>
                            <li>Maintain focus when spotting—do not use your phone or engage in distracting conversations.</li>
                            <li>For squat spotting, use multiple spotters for heavy attempts.</li>
                            <li>For bench press, ensure proper hand positioning to assist if needed.</li>
                            <li>Know when to assist with a lift and when to take over completely if safety is at risk.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>INJURY PREVENTION AND RESPONSE</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Never train through sharp pain—distinguish between normal training discomfort and potential injury.</li>
                            <li>Be aware of your own limitations and do not attempt lifts beyond your current capabilities.</li>
                            <li>In case of injury, stop training immediately and seek appropriate medical attention.</li>
                            <li>A first aid kit is available at the Sports Center reception.</li>
                            <li>Report all injuries that occur during association activities to a Board member.</li>
                            <li>Follow proper return-to-training protocols after an injury, preferably with medical clearance.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>COMPETITION SAFETY</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Follow all rules and procedures established by competition organizers.</li>
                            <li>Ensure all equipment meets competition standards and regulations.</li>
                            <li>Warm up adequately and follow a planned attempt strategy.</li>
                            <li>Don't attempt weights in competition that significantly exceed your training maximums.</li>
                            <li>Listen to and respect the decisions of referees and officials.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>If you have a pre-existing medical condition that may affect training, inform the Board confidentially.</li>
                            <li>Pregnant members should consult with healthcare providers about appropriate training modifications.</li>
                            <li>Members returning from extended breaks should reduce intensity and volume temporarily.</li>
                            <li>Be aware of your hydration and nutritional needs during training sessions.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
