                <!-- Competition Rules -->
                <div class="document-card" id="competition-rules" data-category="competition">
                    <div class="document-header">
                        <h3 class="document-title">COMPETITION RULES</h3>
                        <div>
                            <span class="document-category">Competition</span>
                            <span class="document-meta">Last updated: October 20, 2024</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="document-content">
                        <p>This document outlines the rules and procedures for competitions organized by T.S.K.V. Spartacus. These rules are based on KNKF standards but adapted for our internal events.</p>
                        
                        <h3>ELIGIBILITY AND REGISTRATION</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Internal competitions are open to all T.S.K.V. Spartacus members in good standing.</li>
                            <li>Registration deadlines are typically two weeks before the competition date.</li>
                            <li>Weight classes follow standard KNKF divisions but may be modified based on participation.</li>
                            <li>A participation fee may apply to cover costs (medals, equipment, refreshments).</li>
                            <li>First-time competitors are encouraged to participate and will receive additional guidance.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>COMPETITION FORMAT</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Standard powerlifting competitions include three attempts each at squat, bench press, and deadlift.</li>
                            <li>The highest successful attempt in each lift is added for a total score.</li>
                            <li>Winners are determined by highest total within each weight class.</li>
                            <li>Wilks or IPF GL points may be used to determine overall winners across weight classes.</li>
                            <li>Additional formats (push-pull, deadlift only, etc.) may be offered for special events.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>TECHNICAL RULES</h3>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>Squat:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The lifter must descend until the top surface of the legs at the hip joint is lower than the top of the knees.</li>
                                    <li>After completing the descent and achieving proper depth, the lifter must recover to an upright position with knees locked.</li>
                                    <li>No bouncing or double movements at the bottom of the lift.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>Bench Press:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The lifter must lower the bar to the chest, hold it motionless on the chest, and then press upward.</li>
                                    <li>The bar must be pressed to full arm's length with elbows locked.</li>
                                    <li>No excessive arching of the back or raising of the buttocks from the bench.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>Deadlift:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The bar must be lifted until the lifter is standing erect with shoulders back.</li>
                                    <li>Knees must be locked at the completion of the lift.</li>
                                    <li>No downward movement of the bar during the ascent.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h3>EQUIPMENT RULES</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Internal competitions typically follow raw/classic rules (non-supportive singlet, belt, wrist wraps, knee sleeves permitted).</li>
                            <li>All equipment must comply with KNKF regulations for material, thickness, etc.</li>
                            <li>Equipment checks may be conducted before the competition.</li>
                            <li>Chalk is permitted and will be provided.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>OFFICIATING</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Three referees will judge each lift with white (good) or red (failed) lights.</li>
                            <li>Two or more white lights are needed for a successful attempt.</li>
                            <li>A technical controller may be appointed to check equipment and starting positions.</li>
                            <li>Experienced members are encouraged to volunteer as referees for internal competitions.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>ATTEMPT SELECTION</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Initial attempts must be submitted at weigh-in.</li>
                            <li>After each attempt, lifters have one minute to submit their next attempt weight.</li>
                            <li>Weights can only be increased from previous attempts (except after failed third attempts).</li>
                            <li>Minimum increment is 2.5kg (or 1kg for record attempts).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
